social_posts.post_text: This is me just peaking out to say “hello” for the first time in 2 years. What better way than with a perfectly imperfect freestyle - just like the good ol’ days. Song credit - Dusted Compass by The Human Experience and Lila Rose 🙏 #oldschoolflow #premierpole
Have a wonderful weekend my loves. Song credit: “Mother I hear You” by @jessica.sirena and @momentologymusic 🙏 #oldschoolflow #premierpole #rhiannannichole

This is now the 14th time I’ve received Kambo medicine and I continued to be humbled and in awe of its power. I’m working specifically with healing my mother wound and womb clearing this time around. I’ve been afraid to let go because I thought letting go would hurt. I’ve been afraid to stop running because if I’m not running, what do I do? I’ve been afraid to let love in because I don’t know how to be soft and strong at the same time. Healing is cyclical. So I will continue to love these wounds. For now, my physical body feels lighter. I feel blessed. Honored. Humbled. Loved. My womb feels flexible without the clutching sensation I had before. Trust and surrender. Always with trust and surrender. Thank you @akal_pritam_kaur for being your divine self and holding space for me. So much gratitude and love for you sister. Aho 🙏🐸🙌🌹🤍🐉💫 #kambo

Moving with strong boundaries, deep compassion, and the absolute knowing that I only want what is meant for me and what is meant for me will find me. Finally walking and speaking in my power- fearlessly, authentically, with kindness and humility. Cradling all past versions of myself within my own womb. All pieces of my soul collected and nurtured. Blessed, grateful, full, and open. Connected to all that is, has been, and ever will be. God is in me as me. I am. (And so are you). 🙏🤍💫🐉🌹 #premierpole #shinepoleshow #rhiannannichole

So much to say about this performance. The last 5 years of my life have been massively transformative. My entire life has been upended. I have fought so many battles, healed so much trauma, cleared immense ancestral karma, died and rebirthed over and over again. I fought every war because it’s what I came here to do. The bloodier the better. Everything that defined who I was has burned and I have emerged from the fires anew, a force of nature, driven by purpose, sustained by love, and guided by the Divine. It’s finally time to come home and take my place at the throne of my own life. And all of this is what this performance meant to me. Surrounded by the people who were meant to be there with me. No one truly knows the depths to which I’ve descended. But if this world is truly one of balance, then I will demonstrate it to you by how high I rise. 🙏🐉🌹🤍💫🔥 song is “Journey” by Natasha Blume #premierpole #shinepoleshow

One of my favorite classes I teach is called #pointandpolish ✨ I choreograph a flow piece and teach that same choreo for a month. Because of the nature of the ongoing process, I get to work more closely with my ladies and get to know them and their learning needs in a way that helps me to serve them better. And through this detailed instruction process, I also get to know my own art more intimately. Which in turn allows me to be more present when creating the next piece of choreo. Which of course only enhances my experience when exercising my passion. It’s an incredible gift. Not sure who benefits more from our time together - my students, or me. Anywho, this is the last choreo we did that I’m finally getting around to recording. Song: Trust by @sophielowelowe #premierpole #oldschoolsexyflow #oldschoolpoleflow

Warm up wiggles. My personal warm ups are just a few songs of flowing around the pole to songs that make me smile. I find that if I don’t dance out my initial movement wiggles, I’m less grounded in my body when I try to create curriculum or record videos which can make me feel antsy or less connected. It feels exactly the same as chanting or shaking for several minutes before sitting to meditate. And it’s nice to intentionally tap into my inner child while dancing! Wins all the way around 🥰🙏🌹🤍💫🐉 Song: Budapest by @george_ezra #premierpole #oldschoolsexyflow #oldschoolpoleflow

This is the current #pointandpolish routine I’ve been teaching my girls. They’ve been working on this one for over a month. It’s incredibly gratifying for me to watch them go through the learning process each time. There’s always initial shock and hesitation and worry that the choreo is too hard. But we take it step by step, one grip-change-pivot at a time. Then they start getting through it. Then they find space for added body hits and hair flips. And they start to feel it. And then I see them incorporate the movements into their freestyle dances with confidence. Using the movements as tools for self-expression. Healing. It’s inspiring and always makes me feel like a proud momma. I’m grateful to have a career that expands my heart and gives me the opportunity to be of service in a good way. It might just be a 60 second piece of choreo. But the impact is truly immeasurable when you consider the experience by all connected to it. And each new choreo brings a new opportunity for expansion. Pretty cool if you ask me 🥹🙏🤍🌹🐉 Song: Tincture by Feral Fauna #premierpole #oldschoolpoleflow

Feelin’ myself in this outfit. I went through a rockabilly phase in my early 20’s. I love how feminine the style is. Thank you to all the ladies who came out tonight for our Red White and Booty dance party. My heart is so full 🥰🙏 #premierpole

Expressing a more playful side of my feminine energy tonight. Allowing the different aspects of ourselves to take turns having center stage is an act of self love. Integration of all selves. This is a freestyle and I have never danced to this song before. I love doing that because I have no idea what is going to happen. I surrender fully to what ever wants to be expressed based on what emotions and aspects of myself are activated by the music. And I’m the one observing from the inside. Yes I’m the one dancing. But I’m also not. That’s just the meat suit matching the frequency of the music and behaving accordingly. I’m the me on the inside who gets to heal from it. 🙏🌹💫🐉 song: You Know I’m No Good by Amy Winehouse 🔥🤘

Sacral and solar plexus release with a freestyle. I was able to surrender to it as the dance progressed but it felt like it was just the tip of the ice burg. This whole year has been about womb clearing, sacral healing, learning how to use my sexual energy as a tool to expand my consciousness, and discovering a healthier relationship with pleasure and how it fits into my life now. This dance felt like an expression of some of the denser frustrations that come with that journey. And as I mentioned, it felt like there’s much more that needs to be brought to the surface so, to be continued. 🙏💫🌹🐉 Song: Touch by MAALA #premierpole

At the end of last year, Kambo showed me how much of my sexual trauma was self-inflicted. On January 1st, I sat with the medicine again and took a vow of celibacy in order to heal those traumas and rebuild my relationship with myself. No sexual relations, including with myself, until my birthday of this year. Which is today. So I closed the vow today with Kambo again. 

The last 8 months have been monumentally transformative. My guides showed me how to clear my womb, how to cut the energetic cords, and how to retrieve the fragmented parts of my soul, reabsorbing them into the whole. They taught me how sacred our sexual energy is and how to channel it up into my crown. They led me to a place of purity within my womb and my heart. 

The next, and last, person I choose to be intimate with will receive the gift of my conscious choosing. No more a slave to the urges. No more pornographic fantasies. Sex will never again be godless. This queen only wants to be held by her king, as it is intended, and I feel SEXIER for it. The thought of giving myself to one person is hotter than any fantasy I could imagine. It feels pure. 

The healing in my womb has also triggered a healing in my heart. My feminine is out and ready to RECEIVE love. My heart is open. I feel like both a queen and a child. Standing in my power like never before but also more playful and quicker to laugh than ever before. Powerful AND playful. 

Thank you @akal_pritam_kaur for walking beside me through these ceremonies. Your heart inspires mine. Gracias Kambo. Kambo knows the purity of my heart and the depth of my gratitude and humility. I am humbled to have been chosen to know this sacred medicine and will continue to honor the spirit of Kambo by integrating the lessons, loving myself, and offering myself for service whenever possible. Such gifts can not be squandered. 

Happy solar return to me! All versions of me from this lifetime, and all versions of me from past and future timelines from every dimension and corner of the cosmos. I love every single one of us. Aho! And so it is.🙏🐸🌹🐉💫 #kambo #kambomedicine #wombhealing

Today I am 12 months sober. On this day last year, I lay in a heap on the floor, surrendering every cell of my being to the will of God in exchange for mercy.

Goddess Kali Ma answered. She came to me in a fiery blaze and delivered me from my addiction. She was terrifying. Not what you would expect when meeting a goddess. She pinned me against the floor and began pulling it out of me. Black goo. It was extremely painful. Burning alive from the inside out. Purging from every timeline. 

I told her she scared me so if she wanted to help me, we’d need to work together. I asked who she was. I had never heard of Kali before this. She flipped me over onto my knees and spoke through me in a voice that was not my own, “I AM KALI!!! ALL WILL BURN!!!!!” Booming voice. Syllables drawn out. Over and over again she proclaimed this to me. “I AM KALIIIIIII!! ALL WILL BUUUUURN!!!” My vocal cords reaching volumes and pitches I didn’t know I was capable of. My ribs felt like they were exploding from the pressure of the release of my heart. She continued to pull the black goo out of me. I continued to scream and cry at the top of my lungs. Past lives flashing. 

And that was it. It was gone. Liquid golden light now fills the spaces black goo used to cling. I did not crave a drink a single time this entire year. It’s as if alcohol doesn’t exist on my timeline anymore. I was granted a miracle. I was shown yet another hand of God. 

God has come to me in many forms since my first awakening. Kali is one. To love her is to embrace the devastation of transformation. Her love moves through my life like a wildfire. She is the Dark Mother. Ferocious and unyielding in her determination to cleanse us of our ignorances. She gave me back my life and brought me home to myself. Gratitude is an understatement. Praise Kali 🙌🙏🌹🐉💫 song: Power by @isakdanielson

Old School Flow 1 routine for my ladies this week. I love having an excuse to choreograph Halloween songs. And I love teaching flows to new students - to be the one to pop their old school flow “cherry,” so to speak. I love slowly watching their bodies relax and open up. And I love that even my most advanced students still find value in learning beginner flows. Because they know the most basic of flows can be elevated by mastery. And mastery offers deep levels of satisfaction. Mmmmmm 😏 Super cool cover of Black Magic Woman by @vctrysband 🙏🌹🐉 #premierpole #rhiannannichole #oldschoolpoleflow #oldschoolflow

“How awful it must be for an immortal to fall in love with a human” was my first thought when I heard this rendition of Wicked Game by Ursine Vulpine. So I decided to dance as a love sick vampire who’d fallen in love with a mortal for our Halloween show. Around that same time, the Goddess Rhiannon was increasingly popping into my field. So I’ve been working with her and learned something: she was a goddess who fell in love with an earth King and came down to be his Queen. Hmmm…another immortal falling for a mortal theme. In the meantime, every time I listened to that song to visualize choreo, my body would be covered in chills and my heart would pound so hard that I could only listen to the song a few times before I needed a break from the swelling of emotion asking to be felt. Something was going on here. I have also been struggling with the idea of being in a relationship. I lose myself. I slowly become stagnant and uninspired and do less of the things I love. Less of the things I NEED. I feel more powerful, more free, more like MYSELF when I’m alone. Or with sisters. I started to feel like the immortal tempted by the mortal. Struggling with wanting to keep my sovereignty but also wanting to be in love. And FRUSTRATED with the inability to find the balance. Then the morning of the show, after listening to the song and visualizing my routine, I started to channel. My light language asking me to transmute. It only further confirmed what I suspected, this performance was to be some kind of catalyst for me. Then it was finally time to dance. The energy pulsing through my body was out of this world. I stayed in my body, opened my channel, and merged with the energy that was asking to be brought to light. My heart felt like it was bleeding but I stayed open and intended full surrender. I wanted to cry and scream. When it was done, I felt a huge release and I started to channel again. You can see me shut it down because it wasn’t the place. The performance itself was the transmutation. An energetic loop that I have battled for lifetimes. I don’t want to come down from the mountain. And I enjoy my own company too much to share the view. ⛰️🙏🌹✨#premierpole

I’ll be teaching this routine in Old School Flow 1 tonight! This is the kind of curriculum I would love to teach online in zoom classes! If taking weekly Old School Flow classes with me virtually is something you’re into, please let me know! The class would be on the same day, at the same time, every week, just like if you were going to your local studio. I will guide you through a full 90 minute class including a sensual, meditative warm up, a banging curriculum, and even a freestyle dance! I’m super excited!!! Hehe Thank you @chrisstapleton for the silky song to wiggle my bones to 🙏 #premierpole #oldschoolflow #virtualpoleclasses

This was the Old School Flow choreo from last week! Emphasis on body movement, weight transfer, and dancing through seemingly static positions. The latter has a tendency to cause in my students something I call “I don’t know what to do anxiety” because you’re doing “less” so your awareness slips from your body up into your mind - where we don’t want it. The goal is to exhale through the stillness and stay in the body, not to start thinking about what you have to do next simply because you have the time to think about it. ✨ Groovy song by @embrzmusic 🙏 #premierpole #oldschoolflow #rhiannannichole

I’m teaching a chair dance workshop this Friday! I left the chair tricks out of this one (for the most part) and opted for gooey body movement instead. 🤤 No pole experience necessary, open to all skill levels. Register at premierpole.com 🌹 Thank you @danrell for the delicious song 🙏 #premierpole #chairdance

Hehe I just love holiday choreographies. Isn’t this the cutest freaking song?! Who wants to come snuggle me and be my snowman? I’m teaching this in Old School Flow this week AND next! Eeeee! Thank you @siamusic for the cutest song ever to hop around to 🙏✨🌹🐉 #premierpole #rhiannannichole #oldschoolflow

Last night was the close of another 6 Week Embodied Seduction series. This container is not to be entered into lightly. These women are here to heal. And it is my honor and privilege to guide them. Yes, we learn lap dance and striptease. But probably not like you’ve ever seen it before. Dripping in love, authenticity, and connection. For 6 weeks they are re-writing suppressed traumas, retrieving fragments of their soul, and experiencing what true self love actually looks and feels like. To witness them is a gift and an inspiration on my own healing journey. I woke up this morning with my body still covered in affirmations from my Sisters. What a beautiful way to wake up. Thank you for trusting me to guide you. 🙏 I teach this series every couple of months. If you missed this one, there will be another one! The series is constantly morphing to integrate new downloads I receive regarding the information that needs to be delivered and how. You can attend the series as many times as you want and continue to benefit greatly. I love you all so much. Gratitude overflowing this morning. Have a beautiful day 🙏🌹🐉 #premierpole #innerchildhealing #wombhealing #soulretrieval #rhiannannichole
